{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, no respondents in the high-frequency groups disagreed",
    "with the convenience statement.",
    "This supports the hypothesis that perceived convenience is a primary behavioral driver behind repeated use, often overpowering health considerations.",
    "It further explains the intention-behavior gap, where users consciously prioritize speed and ease over nutritional balance.",
    "These behavioral patterns support Social Cognitive Theory (SCT), illustrating how environmental cues, peer behavior, and digital marketing (such as default platform suggestions) influence dietary decisions."
  ]
}